BeanFactory :

Definition: BeanFactory is the root interface for accessing the Spring container.
Role: It is responsible for instantiating, configuring, and managing beans.
Usage: It is lightweight and used for simple scenarios, but not commonly used in modern Spring applications.
Example:

BeanFactory factory = new XmlBeanFactory(new FileSystemResource("beans.xml"));
UserService userService = (UserService) factory.getBean("userService");


Note: BeanFactory is lazy-initialized (beans are created only when requested).